The paper proposes a new meta-RL algorithm that focuses on generating high-level meta strategies over subgoals, which suggests a hierarchical approach to RL. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories. The paper also evaluates the proposed method on several simulated robotics environments, which suggests that it falls under cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper mentions using vision-based observations, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper proposes a method for more efficient and generalized meta-learning, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
